{
  "text": "Horseradish peroxidase conjugated rabbit polyclonal antihuman IgM antibody (American Qualex, San Clemente, California, USA) was used for immunohistochemical detection of IgM. Monoclonal antibodies (mAbs) against the complement factor C3d (mAb C3-15; subtype, IgG1) and against CRP (mAb 5G4; subtype, IgG2a) have been used previously for immunohistochemical studies. [CITATION_1] mAb aE11 (subtype, IgG2a; Dako, Carpinteria, California, USA) was used for the detection of complement factor C5b-9. The mAbs were stored at 1 mg/ml in phosphate buffered saline (PBS), pH 7.4. Irrelevant mAbs (two IgG1, one IgG2a, and one IgM) were used as negative controls, and tested at concentrations similar to those used for the anti-complement and anti-CRP mAbs. These controls yielded negative results.",
